headline: MIAX-parent Miami International targets $1.7 billion valuation in rare exchange IPO
summary: The Princeton, New Jersey-based company, backed by private equity firm Warburg Pincus, is seeking to raise up to $315 million by offering 15 million shares priced between $19 and $21 apiece.  The listing comes at a time when frequent bouts of market volatility, triggered by geopolitical tensions and tariff turmoil, have boosted trading volumes and profits for exchanges in recent quarters.  Exchange IPOs are rare.
